Sec. 41.054. OFFICERS; BOND. (a) The board shall elect from
its number a chairman, a secretary-treasurer, and other officers that
it considers necessary.
(b) The secretary-treasurer shall execute a corporate surety
bond in an amount required by the board. The bond shall be
conditioned on the secretary-treasurer faithfully accounting for all
money that comes into the custody of the officer. The bond shall be
filed with the commissioner.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1087, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

